 Third-grade teacher Kyle Schwartz devised a lesson plan last month , asking her students to open up about their personal struggles .
Kyle Schwartz has been a teacher for three years , and says many of her students at Doull Elementary School come from underprivileged backgrounds , with 92 per cent of the student body qualifying for free or reduced lunch .
Schwartz asked them to write about missing her father , who was deported back to Mexico .